article.headline: Felton's 30 lead East Carolina over Campbell 77-63
article.description: — RJ Felton scored 30 points as East Carolina beat Campbell 77-63 on Saturday.
article.linkText: Felton's 30 lead East Carolina over Campbell 77-63
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- — RJ Felton scored 30 points as East Carolina beat Campbell 77-63 on Saturday. Felton had 11 rebounds and three steals for the Pirates (2-0). Brandon Johnson added 13 points while shooting 5 for 9, including 3 for 7 from beyond the arc, and he also had five rebounds. Ezra Ausar went 5 of 6 from the field to finish with 11 points. The Fighting Camels (1-1) were led by Anthony Dell'Orso, who recorded 35 points, eight rebounds and three steals. Laurynas Vaistaras added nine points for Campbell. NEXT UP Both teams next play Wednesday. East Carolina hosts South Carolina Upstate and Campbell takes on Virginia Tech on the road. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
